sentences.english: In 2008, Grenada sent a 15-member team to participate in the Olympic Games in Beijing.
sentences.chinese: 2008年，格林納達派出15人代表隊參加奧運會。

sentences.english: My experience in Grenada will be a great treasure for the rest of my life.
sentences.chinese: 我在格林納達的經歷將是我今後人生的寶貴財富。

sentences.english: Altogether, the losses amounted to 200 percent of Grenada’s gross domestic product.

sentences.english: Above the tiny island nation of Grenada, big things were happening in the sky.

sentences.english: George's, on Grenada, is the capital and the largest city. Population, 0,00.

sentences.english: I remember, wherever I go in Grenada, I will receive worm welcome from everybody.
sentences.chinese: 我記得，我在格林納達各地都受到民衆的熱情接待。

sentences.english: Being black in Canada and being black as a child in Grenada are like night and day.
sentences.chinese: 加拿大的黑人與格林納達的黑人簡直是天上人間。

sentences.english: Mitchell reiterated that Grenada will continue to pursue the one-China policy.
sentences.chinese: 米切爾重申格林納達政府將繼續堅持一箇中國政策。
